Incident.Summary: Responded to the above address for a possible domestic assault.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Incident Type: Disturbance Involved parties Curtis Mahalia Ann Turner #1 F / 09-22-1961 Willie Frederick Ames Jr. #1 M / 08-11-1983 Aleasha Watts #1 F / 08-11-1983 margin-left:8px">Dwight Watts #1 M / Subject not on scene Narrative: On 01-12-2023 at 2259 hours I, TFC. Norfolk 7120 responded to 1010 Beaglin park Drive Apt. 104 Salisbury MD 21801 for a complaint of a possible domestic violence call. I arrived at the scene and met with the caller identified as Curtis Turner. Turner advised as I walked up that police intervention was no longer needed and that the unwanted party in the incident had already left the scene. I informed Turner that due to the nature of the call, I would have to see everyone involved for injuries. I then met with Willie Frederick Ames Jr. Ames stated that no domestic assault occurred and that the issue was between his girlfriends brother identified as Dwight Watts and himself. These two parties do not live together nor do they have a domestic relationship. Ames had no signs of injuries. I then contacted Aleasha Watts the girlfriend of Ames. Aleasha stated that her brother came down to the residence from Baltimore MD angry because Ames was trying to separate from Aleasha. Aleasha had no signs of injury. Turner also did not have any injuries. Turner asked why did two sets of cops respond to the house for this incident at different times. Turner stated that Salisbury City Police and Wicomico County Sheriffs responded to the residence before our arrival. Turner advised that the Sheriffs explained to everyone on the scene that they could press charges on Dwight if they wished to and gave them the information on how to do so. Ames, Aleasha, and Turner did not want to press any charges. All events occurred in Wicomico County MD I request this case be closed Case closed.
